text: I think Marvel is more critically reviewed because it just doesn't appeal to the comic fanatics where they see their character on the big screen and it's all serious and with cool action scenes. Marvel movies like to have fun with their movies and have parts in which you can laugh at all the while giving their characters personality.  Their villains may be bland but they only last one movie. I mean I liked Ultron and hate how he's gone so soon but it's a formula that Marvel follows. It likes to focus on the likable characters and use the villains to build them up and I feel Thanos will be the most memorable villain cause he'll be the final boss. Also, everyone likes Loki and he's been in a lot of movies. I feel like if DC stopped trying to force movies that comic fanatics want to see and have a larger story like Marvel does with its movies it may do better. But Idk I just like Marvel better because I can actually enjoy the dialogue and not just wait bored for another action sequence.

This feels like a filler movie for the inbetween  wait to Infinity War. This suffers from the more generic marvel movie villian syndrome as well. All in all guardians is a fun ride  but it's not as good as i was expecting, it doesn't really expand much on the depth of the characters.

text: The blue man with the arrow (Yondu) dies in the end in order to save Starlord from his evil dad that is trying to wipe out the universe. Gamora's sister Nebula comes back and tries to kill her but they end up becoming friends and help each other defeat Starlord's father. Yondu's crew goes mutiny in the beginning of the film but Yondu and Rocket Raccoon manage to escape with the help of one man that is still loyal. Gamora and Starlord are finally officially a thing. Starlord's father implanted the tumor in Starlord's mother. He also killed many of his own children because he was looking for one that had the power he eventually found in Starlord. The Guardians of the Galaxy vol 2 is a great movie. I highly recommend it.

text: spoiler alert, continue reading at you're own risk: this is a freakin awesome movie. this movie is better than the first, but not by much. the humor is great and i love baby groot. the acting is amazing, the special effects are amazing, and the action is great and the characters are awesome. i was happy to see that the main villain in the movie is ego the living planet. the story is great. this is a great addition to the mcu. this is a movie that all comic book, superhero or nerds alike will love. it sucked that yondu died i liked him better in this one than the first movie, and i loved how the guardians bickered like a family and i loved how they did gamora's and nebula's relationship. marvel has been giving us gems and i hope they don't stop. if you have not seen this movie then i recommend you do rating 5/5

text: My quick review: This is nowhere near as good a movie as Guard of Galaxy 1. Some of the visuals are even better than part 1. The first half of the movie dragged on. The main problem was the dialogue was a lot of bathroom humor and goofy bad jokes (and I know this franchise is supposed to have some goofy humor, but it was wayyy overdone) Some of the jokes, and I could care less about censorship or adult humor, were downright disgusting, as in gross. The second half had some excellent action scenes but the action scenes in part 1 seemed better choreographed or something. I would rate it a C+ or B- and part 1 I would give an A. Plot and characters were all over the place. Even for a purposefully light funny and goofy action movie, the jokes mostly fell flat. Worth seeing but nowhere near as cohesive as part 1. Dialogue in action sci fi and comic book movies seems to be getting more and more off-the-wall and silly every year. Every scene does not have to be a snappy dumb one-liner. What happened to serious dialogue?
